:format_choice:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/filemgr.handbook
Disk Format

Choose a disk format depending on the 
operating system and hardware you have.

Format			Capacity
------			--------
UNIX			1.4 MB unformatted
DOS High Density	1.4 MB unformatted
NEC-DOS Medium Density	800 KB unformatted
:format_diskname:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/filemgr.handbook
Disk Name

Give your disk a name or label.
Use upper or lower case letters or numbers,
no spaces.  Some of the non-alphanumeric 
characters will work.  Avoid &, !, *, and
other characters that have special meanings
in shells.
 
:format_format:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/filemgr.handbook
Format Disk

Formats the floppy disk in the format
you choose. Formatting takes a couple
of minutes.  

WARNING: Formatting erases all data on the disk.

:format_cancel:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/filemgr.handbook
Cancel

Click on Cancel to dismiss the window.

